An Act relative to healthcare industry recruitment and education for the 21st Century.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 6A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by inserting after section 16FF the following section:-
3 Section 16GG. (a) There shall be a healthcare industry recruitment and education
4 advisory council within, but not subject to control of, the executive office of health and human
5 services. The council shall advise the governor and the general court, and shall assist in
6 informing the work of the secretary of education, the secretary of health and human services, the
7 secretary of labor and workforce development and the secretary of housing and economic
8 development on issues relating to the Healthcare Industry Recruitment and Education Fund,
9 hereinafter referred to as the HIRE Fund, pursuant to section 2JJJJJJ of chapter 29.
